This paper deals with the evolution of discrete surfaces, which is a topic related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete structures (cs.DS). The constraints on the evolution of the surface also involve concepts from graph theory (cs.GR) and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the causal dynamics on the surface, which is a topic related to scientific computing (cs.SC).
